.TH "TEMPORAL.DURATION.NEGATED" "3JS" "December 8, 2025" "JavaScript" "JavaScript Reference Manual"
.SH NAME
Temporal.Duration.negated \- Temporal.Duration.prototype.negated()
.SH SYNOPSIS
The \f[B]\f[CB]negated()\f[B]\f[R] method of
\f[CR]Temporal.Duration\f[R] instances returns a new
\f[CR]Temporal.Duration\f[R] object with the negated value of this
duration (all fields keep the same magnitude, but sign becomes
reversed).
.SH SYNTAX
.IP
.EX
negated()
.EE
.SS Parameters
None.
.SS Return value
A new \f[CR]Temporal.Duration\f[R] object, where all fields have the
same magnitude as this duration, but the sign is reversed (positive
fields become negative, and vice versa).
.SH EXAMPLES
.SS Using negated()
.IP
.EX
\f[B]const\f[R] d1 = Temporal.Duration.from({ hours: 1, minutes: 30 });
\f[B]const\f[R] d2 = Temporal.Duration.from({ hours: \-1, minutes: \-30 });

console.log(d1.negated().toString()); \f[I]// \(dq\-PT1H30M\(dq\f[R]
console.log(d2.negated().toString()); \f[I]// \(dqPT1H30M\(dq\f[R]
.EE
.SH SEE ALSO
.IP \(bu 2
\f[CR]Temporal.Duration\f[R]
.IP \(bu 2
\f[CR]Temporal.Duration.prototype.abs()\f[R]
.IP \(bu 2
\f[CR]Temporal.Duration.prototype.sign\f[R]
